(I called out, but it seems only these few will follow...
The women and children are probably overwhelmed just by
following; they can't be counted on as combatants.)

Worker: I thought I hadn't seen you around for a while, and
here you are plotting something interesting. Count me in on
the plan. It's been a while since I've had a chance to flex
my magic skills.

Worker: I owe you one for the rock digging. Staying here
isn't going to get us anywhere. It's time to give those
guards a taste of the pain we've endured!

Young Worker: I can't fight, but I believe in you, big
sisters! I'll look around a bit more to see if there's
anyone else who wants to get out!

Worker: Leave the guiding to me. I've been near the exit
before when I helped carry some loads.

Reisha: I'm grateful to everyone who has gathered. I will
lead the battle. Arm yourselves with weapons for self-
defense and follow me! Now, let's head for the light and
make our way to the exit!
